<TITLE> Barisal Jubo League leader killed in 'shootout' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, May 15 (bdnews24.com) A sacked leader of Jubo League was killed in 'shootout' with RAB at the city's Dopdopia ferry point early on Friday. The dead, Jalal Akon, 36, is the son of Motahar Akon of Nondopara of Boalia in Bakerganj Upazila. He was general secretary of the ruling Awami League's youth front at Rongosree union. "A team of RAB surrounded the area getting news of clandestine activities of Jalal's group. They tried to flee firing at RAB," RAB-8 Lt Commander KM Mamunur Rashid told bdnews24.com. The elite force retaliated and the shootout went on for around 15 minutes. The group fled the scene leaving a dead body on the spot. The locals later identified the body as that of Jalal, he said. A light gun, a shutter gun and 16 rounds of bullets were recovered from the scene. There are 10 cases, including one for murder, against Jalal at Bakerganj Police Station, said Rashid. Jalal had been expelled on charges of torturing an old man, said Bakerganj thana Jubo League president Lokman Hossain Dakua. bdnews
